<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Event Hub</title>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>Event Hub</h1>
      <nav>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="#upcoming-events">Upcoming Events</a></li>
          <li><a href="#past-events">Past Events</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section id="upcoming-events">
        <h2>Upcoming Events</h2>

        <article>
          <h3>Tech Innovation Summit</h3>
          <p>
            Join developers, designers, and technology enthusiasts for a day of talks, workshops, and networking focused on the future of web development, artificial intelligence, and digital creativity.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3>Creative Coding Workshop</h3>
          <p>
            A hands-on workshop for beginners who want to learn how to build interactive web projects using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Participants will create small projects while learning practical coding skills.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="past-events">
        <h2>Past Events</h2>

        <article>
          <h3>Community Web Design Meetup</h3>
          <p>
            A local meetup where students and new developers shared their first website projects, exchanged feedback, and learned simple techniques for improving layout, accessibility, and user experience.
          </p>
          <img
            src="https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/labs/past-event1.jpg"
            alt="People attending a web design meetup"
          >
        </article>

        <article>
          <h3>Beginner JavaScript Night</h3>
          <p>
            An evening event dedicated to basic JavaScript concepts, including variables, functions, conditionals, and small interactive examples for people taking their first steps in programming.
          </p>
          <img
            src="https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/labs/past-event2.jpg"
            alt="Participants learning JavaScript at an event"
          >
        </article>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
